properties.name: Airy Interlude
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneWas called one of the 4 "must do" 5.10 crack routes on the continent. The second pitch hand crack traverse is this one\'s claim to fame.

properties.name: Astroman
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneOne of the most sought after day routes in Yosemite Valley. 5.11c. The Harding Slot and the Enduro-Corner Pitches will seperate the men from the boys on this one.

properties.name: High Exposure
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneRated 5.6, it is not very physically demanding but that does not take away from the quality of the route. Great Rock quality and a great location.

properties.name: Lightning Bolt Cracks
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneClassic 3-pitch Desert Tower located in Indian Creek Canyon. Mostly 5.10 climbing with a short section of 5.11 at the start.

properties.name: Mr. Clean, Devil's Tower
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneWas called the best 5.11 splitter hand crack in north america. Very Long and Sustained

properties.name: Seperate Reality
properties.description: Posted by Jhonkone~30 foot Horizontal Roof. Mega classic with dizzying exposure on the last move. Originally rated 5.12 but when the lip on the roof broke off it got downrated to 5.11d

properties.name: Serenity Crack
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneClassic 5.10a finger crack that looks as good as it climbs. One day...........it will be mine.

properties.name: The Crack House
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneThis Route actually never gets more than 20 feet off the ground. Completely horizontal crack climbing that goes on and on and on....... A professional climber once broke a bone in his hand from holding on to hard on this one. Represents the most difficult physical movement on the list.

properties.name: The Grand Wall
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneBig Wall Route. Located on the Chief. Famous pitches include Perry\'s Lieback and the Split Pillar Pitch

properties.name: The Nose, El Capitan
properties.description: Posted by JhonkoneTHE most famous Big Wall route in the world. What else can be said. 3000 feet of climbing, Fantastic Rock quality, almost too good to be true. Rated 5.9 C1
